---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Activ365"
  description="Activ365 Privacy Policy — we collect no personal data. All workout data stays on your device."
>
  <style>
    .legal-hero { padding: 80px 0 40px; }
    .legal-body {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 20px 100px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      font-size: 15px;
    }
    .legal-body h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 40px 0 12px;
    }
    .legal-body h3 {
      font-size: 16px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 28px 0 8px;
    }
    .legal-body p { margin: 0 0 14px; }
    .legal-body ul { margin: 0 0 14px; padding-left: 22px; }
    .legal-body ul li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .legal-body a { color: #34d399; text-decoration: none; }
    .legal-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .legal-back {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .legal-back:hover { color: #34d399; }
    .app-tag {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #34d399;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
  </style>

  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/activ365" class="legal-back">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        Activ365
      </a>
      <div class="app-tag">
        <span>✅</span> ACTIV365
      </div>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,5vw,56px);margin-bottom:12px;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:15px;">Last updated: 20 April 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="legal-body">

    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Activ365 ("the App") is published by Nano Synapsys (ABN pending), based in Australia.
      This Privacy Policy explains what data the App handles, what it does not collect, and
      your rights as a user. It complies with the Apple App Store guidelines and the
      Australian Privacy Act 1988.
    </p>

    <h2>2. No Account, No Personal Information</h2>
    <p>
      Activ365 does not require an account, email address, or any personal information to use.
      There is no sign-in, no sign-up, and no third-party login of any kind. You can install
      the App and start tracking immediately.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <p>The App does not collect, store remotely, or transmit any of the following:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any contact details</li>
      <li>Apple ID or any third-party account identifier</li>
      <li>Location, contacts, photos, microphone, or camera data</li>
      <li>Browsing history or device fingerprints</li>
      <li>Advertising identifiers — the App contains no advertising SDKs</li>
      <li>Health or fitness data beyond what you type directly into the App</li>
      <li>Analytics, crash reports, or usage telemetry sent to any server</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Stored Locally on Your Device</h2>
    <p>
      The App stores the following data <strong>exclusively on your device</strong> using
      local browser storage (via the Capacitor WebView):
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your workout goal (period and target number)</li>
      <li>Logged workout entries (date, type, optional notes)</li>
      <li>Completed goal history</li>
      <li>App preferences (colour theme, language)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data never leaves your device. It is not synced to any cloud service, not shared
      with any third party, and not accessible to Nano Synapsys.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Privacy Manifest (Apple Requirement)</h2>
    <p>
      As required by Apple, the App includes a <code>PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy</code> manifest
      declaring the following:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>NSPrivacyTracking:</strong> false — the App does not track users</li>
      <li><strong>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes:</strong> empty — no data is collected</li>
      <li>
        <strong>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes:</strong> UserDefaults (reason CA92.1) — used only
        to store app-scoped preferences and workout data locally on the device
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      Activ365 does not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or crash-reporting
      services. The App is built with React and Capacitor — all dependencies operate entirely
      on-device.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The App is rated 4+ on the App Store. Because no personal data is collected, the App is
      safe for users of all ages. We do not knowingly collect any information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      To delete all your data, go to <strong>Settings → Danger Zone → Reset Goal</strong>
      inside the App, or simply delete the App from your device. All locally stored data
      is removed when the App is uninstalled.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy if the App's functionality changes. The "Last updated" date
      at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the App
      after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this Privacy Policy? Contact us at:<br />
      <a href="mailto:support@nano-synapsys.com">support@nano-synapsys.com</a>
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top:48px;padding-top:24px;border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
      <a href="/activ365/terms">Terms &amp; Conditions →</a> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="/activ365">Back to Activ365</a> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="/">Nano Synapsys</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
